attributes.descriptionHtml:
REQUIRES A SECURE FENCE.

EXPERIENCED HANDLER NEEDED. 

Livie needs to be placed in a home without children.


Livie is a 10 year old female Border Collie being fostered in Plymouth, Indiana.  Livie will need a family who will be patient with her.  Please contact stephodellfcr@hotmail.com if you have any questions about Livie.  You can complete an application to adopt Livie or any of the dogs on our website at www.comebyebcrescue.org.

Livie – again a feral barn cat will give you an idea of her flight response. When she was with her puppies she was much easier to handle. Now that she wants nothing to do with her pups, she is back to avoiding being handled. She also is very good at her day to day routine….as long as she can predict what is needed from her she is very compliant.

She goes in and out well on her own. Comes to the door when called to come inside…finds her crate and readily goes in without any help or encouragement. In the play yard she mostly just enjoys napping in the sun…..she doesn’t want to play with other dogs. She will typically watch me as I am moving around the yard and if the gates are open into the other play yards, she will readily follow me to see what I am doing in the other yards. She seems to like to be around me, she just doesn’t want me to approach her. There are times that I do approach her and need to approach her……and I basically have to catch her. Once caught she will tolerate handling.

She is clearly afraid but will just freeze and go inside herself and cope with it….she has never tried to bite or get me out of her space by growling, showing of the teeth or anything like that….. she just is frozen stiff…..then once she feels she can escape, she will get away from me…..but again will turn around and watch me…if I call her to her crate or to the door she will still come back in to my space to comply.

Livie and her son, Gus, are adaptable but they will likely never be dogs that will do well outside of what is familiar, predictable and safe. Taking them EVERYWHERE is not the life they will enjoy. Livie is more stressed for bathing and typically tries to escape during bathing time.

She rides well in a plastic crate in a vehicle. She can also ride loose and does ok, but since she is such a flight risk, I have her ride crated. She loves the Nature’s Variety Raw medallions and actually gets a look of excitement in her eyes when I offer them to her….they are the only thing that she will currently take from my hand. She also enjoys bully sticks when she is outside of her crate…..she won’t chew them when in her crate.

Again, she is a project dog and will need an adopter without expectations, just one that is calm, patient and understanding of the trauma that Livie has likely endured for her entire life. The psychological damage is always going to be there……she is adaptable and can learn a routine…but will never be great with the “unfamiliar” (9/24/14)

attributes.descriptionHtml:
I weigh in at 21lbs, 14 years young and looking for my forever home.

Adoption Donation: $100

Brynn has to go into an adult only home, no children and she has to be the only pet in the house. She is a bit of a special case in that she is not the best with people when she first meets them. Once she gets to know you she is so fun and sweet. She is a volunteer favorite. She just needs someone to give her the chance and time to warm up and get to know you.

Here is a write up from a volunteer --
WHEN BRYNN FIRST ARRIVED AT AHS WE THOUGHT THAT SHE WAS TIMID AND SHY. BUT NOW THAT SHE HAS REALIZED THAT THIS IS A GOOD, SAFE PLACE- HER PERSONALITY HAS JUST BLOSSOMED. THIS BEAUTIFUL, BRINDLE-GIRL IS FULL OF DELIGHTFUL SURPRISES. BRYNN LOVES TO BE OUTSIDE AND SIMPLY JUST DESIRES YOUR COMPANY. SHE IS A LITTLE NUT WITH TOYS AND WILL MAKE YOU LAUGH WHILE YOU WATCH HER PLAY. IF YOU SIT DOWN ON THE GROUND SHE WILL COME RUNNING OVER AND DRAMATICALLY THROW HERSELF UPSIDE DOWN IN YOUR LAP BECAUSE SHE WANTS YOU TO GIVE HER LOTS OF BELLY RUBS. SHE WILL EVEN SNEAK YOU A SWEET LITTLE KISS NOW AND THEN. BRYNN PLAYS WELL WITH OTHER DOGS HER SIZE AND IS JUST A PLEASURE TO BE AROUND. THIS SWEET, CUTIE-PIE IS WAITING FOR A HOME OF HER OWN AND WILL FILL YOU WITH JOY IN RETURN.

She never messes in her cage and is a breeze to walk-no pulling etc. She needs a warm lap to cuddle.

All dogs are microchippped, neutered, current on all vaccines, heartworm tested (if age appropriate) and up to date on preventatives at the time of adoption.

All household members and any dogs from the household need to be present at the time of your appointment.

The shelter is currently open by appointment only with an approved application. Please note, all applications are considered general and stay on file for 6 months. Specific animals are NOT put on hold for adoption. When you visit, the adoption counselors will be able to make suggestions based on the type of pet you are looking for and help you find the best fit for your family.

Animal House Shelter cannot guarantee the breeds of the adoptable animals. The animals are posted on the website as the breed or breed mix based on their physical characteristics they most resemble. We also cannot guarantee the ages of our adoptable animals or how large puppies will be when fully grown.

We look forward to seeing you soon!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Ellie was born 3/6/2014.  She is a beautiful white kitty with gorgeous amber-colored eyes. 

She is special needs and has "FHS" or Feline Hyperesthesia Syndrome.  Her disorder requires a very low home stress environment, and she is totally attached and bonded to her brother (Eli) and we will not separate the two as this would cause her additional anxiety.

Ellie is extremely curious, playful, and extremely smart!  It is her way only!.  Unfortunately, you must have a lot of patience with her as she can be very destructive.  You cannot correct her, you can only try and convince her that whatever she is doing is not a good idea.  If you try and correct her, you will only make her skittish and leary of you which is totally unproductive.

Ellie insists on sleeping with you every single night.  Ellie and her brother Eli are extremely sweet and love the other kitties.  Both are very COMICAL!!!  If you are truly a "cat person" you will thoroughly enjoy these two!

Vinnie is a super sweet dog who loves to snuggle once he gets to know you. He is 10 years old, really healthy and just had a dental and 3 year rabies done. He comes fully vaccinated and microchipped. He gets along with other dogs and cats but children are unknown.

attributes.descriptionHtml: Adopted as just a kitten the owners did not follow through on the vetting and allowed the poor boy to go with out any vetting for a year. When we were finally able to get him back he had a vet appointment ASAP and is now fully vaccinated and neutered. Hes great with other cats, dogs, kids and strangers. Since he is a little older he takes a little longer to warm up. But once you give him a chance hes such a wonderful and affectionate boy.

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hi, I'm Indiana. I was found in a Seal Beach alley near Main Street when I was about 4 months old. I have no idea what happened to my Mama or litter mates. I am a little shy around people but I do accept pets from certain people! I  tolerate my roommates, but would probably do best as an only cat. I hope my family will have a quiet home and will allow me whatever time I need to adjust.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
My name is Cliff but I go by the name Monty. I was adopted as a puppy but had to be returned after 6 wonderful years with my family. I am so confused and would love to have a home to call my own again. I am a nice boy and I love to play ball in the yard. I like to think that I am the perfect mix of play and couch potato!

I’m not sure if I want to live with another dog again but would be willing to try. Young children wouldn’t be best as I get very excited and can be a little clumsy. I love women but it takes me a little to warm up to men. I love car rides and walks. I am strong though so make sure you can hold me if we come across something exciting. I am up to date on vaccines, crate and house trained, microchipped and neutered.

Take a chance on me and you won’t be sorry! Looking for a forever or foster home. I cannot wait to meet you!

If you would like to meet me or adopt me please fill out an online application. Questions to my foster at cbrookszy@yahoo.com

I AM IN FOSTER CARE! PLEASE FILL OUT OUR ADOPTION APPLICATION. ONCE APPROVED, PLEASE EMAIL US (INFO@ANIMALHOUSESHELTER.COM) AND WE CAN SET UP AN APPOINTMENT FOR YOU TO MEET ME!

I am 27lbs, 12 years young and seeking my for ever home!

A note from Dolly's foster family: "Good golly Miss Dolly! Dolly is an adorable old lady who loves naps, car-rides, and romping/sniffing in the yard. She is a #introvertforlife! She loves the few who are part of her pack but does not play well with other dogs and may be territorial around other humans. She will occasionally nip or bite but only if approached the wrong way. Which is why Dolly is looking for a patient home who would be comfortable caring for her through the good and bad moments of her old lady life. She knows "no" and "off" and is housebroken. She does very well with men but is particular about her female friends. Dolly does not bark! Dolly has been with the Animal House Shelter family for over 6 years waiting for that special home, and if you do not have any pets or small children you might be everything she has been waiting for!"

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Sylvester is a big, love bug of a cat.  He came to us at eight weeks old and now he is over 6 years old.   He was found as a stray.  He would prefer to be the center of your attention.  He will tolerate other pets, but her would prefer to be the only one.  He will need time to adjust to a new hone and new people. We are currently only doing online adoptions email us for an application!

 

   We have different adoption procedures during the Covid-19 Pandemic.  Adoptions are done in the following way.  1.  Complete an application and contract.  2.  Pay the adoption fee.  3.  Pick up at the next adoption pick up day.  Usually, done o n Sunday.    Thanks for your understanding. 

We will not do meet and greets, don't bother to ask.  All volunteers are high risk.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Well, hello there, welcome to my page!

What's that, you are here looking for a dog to be your furever buddy! Well that is AMAZING because I am a dog. And guess what!? I am looking for my furever buddy too! Isn't that great!

My name is Maserati, or Mazzie for short. My foster dad just can't stop raving about me! He says I am such a wonderful dog with so much happiness and energy to go around. That couldn't be more true! I play so well with my foster pals, not so good with cats, but definitely love my doggie friends! I will need slow and proper introductions to my new doggie friends.

I love to be active with you, but once I have my nylabone, it is my zen time! I LOVE, LOVE, LOVE playing fetch and tug!

Need some cuddles and a good kiss, I got that covered. If you adopt me {Raises right paw}, I promise to always have your back no matter what. I promise to always give you the love and attention that we both can handle. It would make me the happiest dog on earth to become a part of your family!

I really hope that I get to meet you soon!

Eagerly awaiting your furever lap!

Mazzie!

P.S. - I really hope you have a fenced in yard for me to play in.

For more information or questions, email Tim at tmb611@msn.com.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hello there! My name is Echo, and I live alongside/am bonded to my sister, Pistol. We came from a litter of kittens that was born in a garage and have been at the shelter for a few years now. We're getting to know and trust humans more each day and love to run, jump, and explore! We're ready to open up and share our lives with you and would do best in a quieter home that will allow us to acclimate and get used to our surroundings. We're great with other cats and dogs, too!

We make a great pair, and we'd make an even better addition to your family. Please give us a chance to show you our love, and come meet us today!

Hello there! I'm Pistol, and I live alongside my brother, Echo. Both of us came from a litter of kittens that was born in a garage. We've been at the shelter for a few years now, and we're hoping you can help us find our forever family!

We'd like a quieter home that will allow us to acclimate and get used to our surroundings, and we do love to run, jump, and explore together. You can find us frequently playing with toys and playing on big cat towers. We make a great pair, and we'd make an even better addition to your family. We're also great with other cats and dogs (more pals to play with!). Please give us a chance to show you our love, and come meet us today!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
My name is Max and although I look really big and intimidating, I'm just a big Teddy Bear.  When I was adopted, I was the only animal.  After about 3 years, my owner bought two pit bulls and caged them.  All I wanted to do was play, but after awhile, my owner felt it was becoming a dangerous situation - so back to my foster mom I went.  I was very skittish for a few months...and still a little head shy.  Then I was adopted out with Serena and lived with my foster dad, but things weren't going well.  I mean, he did his best, but once again, I came back with Serena, to my foster mom again.  

I love pets and sweet talk.  Mostly, I enjoy just watching the activity around me.   My  foster momconcern about me being adopted again - but for now, here I am!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
I'm named Twiggy because when I first came to my foster home, I stayed in the kitten room, ate kitten food, and gained a ton of weight!  I've lost quite a bit now (believe or not).  I'm such a sweet girl and just crave love and attention.  I get along with all my cat friends and cuddle and lick on kittens.  And yes, I was tested FIV positive, but since I'm surround by neutered/spayed cats, there is no risk of anyone catching it.  It can't be spread by saliva - just by blood.  Since there are no cat fights (when everyone is "fixed"), I can be around other animals.
My foster mom wants me to get more attention, cause she says I deserve it.  I've been around children and do fine.  Dogs - we don't know.  Anyways, I would love a  FOREVER home, too....won't you give a girl a chance?  I'll even go on a diet and lose some more weight for you!

Do you prefer cuddling up by the fireplace to a night out on the town? Me too! It's hard out there for us introverts. For eleven years, I've watched all the outgoing kitties get adopted, while I am overlooked time after time. Sure, I'm a little shy, but I have a big heart. I once adopted a whole litter of orphaned kittens. I just need a patient soul to adopt me, and I'll adopt you right back.

I am spayed, up to date on shots and negative for FIV/FeLV.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
MAGIC NEEDS TO BE IN A HOME WITHOUT CHILDREN AND NEEDS A PATIENT HANDLER.

Magic is a 6 1/2 year old female Border Collie and is being fostered at Stephany's in Plymouth, Indiana. You can send her an email at stephodellfcr@hotmail.com if you have any specific questions about Magic. If you have any general questions about our adoption process, please go to the Adoption Info page on our website at www.comebyebcrescue.org.

Update 1/21/16

Magic fearful of people and things and cannot be in a home with kids….she is terrified of kids and could nip them. Will stalk cats incessantly. She is good with dogs. Likes riding in the car. Will occasionally be interested in fetching. Affectionate with people she knows. Needs fenced yard.

*******************************************

Magic has strong herding lines, LOVES stalking the cats, loves the baby pool, good in her crate, very attracted to the environment (5/2/15)


Magic – she is adorable and very sweet. She also likes her cuddle time……but is the most interested in the environment of the litter. She is an explorer and really loves to mess with the kitties. She has the worst recall of the puppies and other distractions in the environment of the litter. The other pups will typically all come running to the puppy song, but if Magic is “busy” she will continue to do what she is doing vs coming to me with her siblings. She loves toys and food and is good in her crate. I like her too…I think she is a middle-of-the-road sort of dog that a wide range of folks will enjoy. (9/24/14)

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Our website is updated daily

Ashes is spayed, UTD on vaccines and tested negative for FIV/FeLV. Approx. DOB is May 2014.

*Experienced owner with veterinary references required* 
 *View bio for details ⬇️*

Ashes is a sweet girl and has always been the most active of her siblings.  She is curious, playful and is always looking for attention.  She loves to be held and will snuggle into your neck and sometimes put her paws around your neck as you hold her.  She gets along well with the other cats and kittens, as well as the two large dogs she lives with. 

Ashes developed a food allergy around one year of age but is doing fine now on a limited-ingredient food.  It took some time for an accurate diagnosis as to why Ashes was scratching her neck and chin, resulting in some bald spots where her fur did not grow back.  She is currently eating Nature's Variety Instinct, Limited Ingredient Rabbit formula and she is doing fine with it. 

Ashes continues to be her sweet self, always looking for attention and purring at the drop of a hat.  

If interested in adopting Ashes, please fill out an application online at http://nar.rescuegroups.org.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Sweet boy Benji was returned to us because his owners' work schedule changed and they were not able to let him out enough. His previous owner described him as extremely sweet natured and said that he loves to sleep in bed with his person.
Benji likes short rides in the car, walks on his leash he has a great prance , and sunning outside. He is a wonderful doorbell and will let you know if someone is at your door. Because of his breed and age, he can not handle stairs, so he must be in a stair free household. Benji would do best with a fenced in backyard because he likes to go out to out frequently. He is cat friendly (as long as they are friendly with him), but he does not do great with other dogs as he is not good at reading canine body language (he thinks all dogs want to be his friend). We think with the right dog, he would do just fine. Because of his age, a home with no children is best.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Spencer is a nearly 10 year old male JRT, he does have some ongoing medical concerns including arthritis in his spine, a newly repaired hip joint and some limited vision and hearing.  Spencer is a wonderful semi-senior dog with lots of love to give to a compassionate human, and he won't mind sharing his forever home with other dogs or cats.  Spencer is not a fit with younger children; he does have some lingering pain that could cause him to be snappy and he startles easily with his limited hearing.  Spencer is also somewhat incontinent, however he very successfully wears a belly band and enjoys getting outside often. He can handle moderate or limited exercise, he lived for many years with a serious injury to his backend so he does have some lingering lameness.  Spencer is happiest snuggled up in a dog bed all day, and he loves to stick to a schedule so will bark to let you know if dinner is running late! He will be most happy with someone who is mostly home during the day, although he is kennel trained, he prefers your company after all! Spencer will gladly sleep on your bed all night long, but he will need you to lift him up and down as he should no longer be jumping given the surgery he has had to repair what was a very badly damaged hip joint (surgery known as an FHO).  Spencer does take some medicine long term to ease any arthritis pain or inflammation, and this will need to continued.

 

Spencer's adoption fee is $200 and includes his neuter, microchip and current vaccinations and preventatives.   Spencer has just recently had a dental procedure as well.  Last Hope requires that all animals be kept as indoor pets only, be altered and current on vaccinations and preventatives.  Our adoption process includes reference and background checks, a vet check and home visit. Please apply at Adopthope.org for consideration.
attributes.name: Spencer

attributes.descriptionHtml: Beasley needs a one-person home- just him and his owner.   He may be very standoffish at first, we feel this is because he is scared of new folks and situations. He's been here with us for years now and is used to our staff, but needs time to get to know new people. He is a staff favorite and a total love! Potential adopters should be ready to come and visit Duke a couple of times here at the shelter before bringing him home. He is not always great at meeting new people, so a few visits to the shelter to spend time with him are sure to help him get to know you and want to be your pal.

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hi, my name is Kimmie. I’ll bet you can see in my picture that I’m a sweet girl at heart. I started out in a prison training program. It was great because I was learning all kinds of things to make me an even better friend. However, they discovered that I have seizures. Because of this, they could not keep me in the program. That’s how I ended up at M’Shoogys. However, this isn’t the best place for me either. What I really need is a good home with good people who understand I have special needs and don’t mind giving me medicine to control my seizures. When I’m confused I also tend to want to bite so I can’t go to a home with small children as they don’t know about giving me my space. If you have a big heart full of love and understanding and want to take care of a dog that really needs it; I’m the one for you! Those adopting Kimmie could get her medication at Angel’s Vet at our cost.
attributes.descriptionText: Hi, my name is Kimmie. I’ll bet you can see in my picture that I’m a sweet girl at heart. I started out in a prison training program. It was great because I was learning all kinds of things to make me an even better friend. However, they discovered that I have seizures. Because of this, they could not keep me in the program. That’s how I ended up at M’Shoogys. However, this isn’t the best place for me either. What I really need is a good home with good people who understand I have special needs and don’t mind giving me medicine to control my seizures. When I’m confused I also tend to want to bite so I can’t go to a home with small children as they don’t know about giving me my space. If you have a big heart full of love and understanding and want to take care of a dog that really needs it; I’m the one for you! Those adopting Kimmie could get her medication at Angel’s Vet at our cost.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hey, Lily Squirt here!!   I'm back with my foster family.  I'm a little sad  because I love my adoptive family and miss them.  You see they had to move and couldn't find a place to rent that would take me.   I think people are afraid I would lick them too much.  You see I'm a love bug and like to give lots of kisses!!  Apparently, not everybody likes kisses.  I stayed with my foster family when I was a pup now I back.   I really love them and it's been great to visit with my old doggie friends but I really want another family of my own.  I have slowed down a bit since my pup days but still love to run so I would do best with in fenced-in yard.  I am already housebroken, leash and crate trained!!   I love to be with my people and snuggle!!  My foster mom thinks that is the cutest thing. I'm glad she likes kisses.  :)  I like treats too!!    I do what I'm told so I can get lots of treats!!  If you are looking for a sweet, loving and active girl I'm the dog for you!!   But my new forever home should be just me as an  only dog.  Can't wait to meet you! 

(CM/CWEL*)

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Max was born about August 30, 2010 and weighs too much at about 60 lbs.  He is definitely Beagley, but seems to be a bit larger and longer than normal so there could be some Basset mixed in.  Whatever breed he may be he is about the sweetest guy you'd ever want to meet.  He is also quiet, which we really appreciate.  He is wonderful with the other dogs, loves to go for rides, is house trained and fine with children.  He is with us because his human father had to take a job where he would be away for 10-12 hours a day and this was back in 2014.
 
Max was adopted a few times and always returned.  The first time is was because he couldn't be alone and it was much less alone than he was used to.  Then the next two times we found humans home much or all the time and then their lives changed.  When Max came back the third time and realizing what was happening and it was obvious his heart was hurting our amazing team of volunteers asked us to not put him back up for adoption and let him be a sanctuary pet at Joyful Rescues.  Which he has been and he is very, very, happy here with all the dogs and there is at least one human here at ALL times.  A volunteer once thought she'd try to foster him and found that she could not even take a shower without him becoming destructive trying to get to her. So, Max came back the same day.  We LOVE this guy and he LOVES the volunteers and staff at the main location - Max is living his best life - the best life for him.
 
 
   SPONSOR ME
Look for the Link "Special Instructions to Seller" if you want to note a particular pet.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hi I am Clover! I had my DNA tested and I am a mix of a lot of cool dogs! I am Catahoula Leopard Dog, American Staffordshire Terrier, Lab and Siberian Husky.  I'm an energetic gal for my age and love exploring and smelling new places. I do have arthritis and an old ACL tear that was repaired but I don't let that stop me from being out and about, but some days it slows me down. Squeaky toys are my all time favorite toy! I love to carry toys around in my mouth, it's my thing! I love the water and playing in the kiddie pool, too! If you like water and beaches I might be the gal for you! I do need a home with no other animals, no children and an experienced dog owner. I like to be the Queen Bee after all!   If you are interested in Clover, we ask you to become a volunteer at the Last Hope Adoption Center to get to know Clover and understand her needs. Please plan to volunteer at least once per week!  Clover does have stranger danger fears, but warms up nicely given time and space.

Clover's adoption fee is $250  includes her spay, microchip and current vaccinations as well as a basic obedience class at Cedar Run in Hiawatha.  Last Hope requires all animals be kept as indoor pets only, be altered and current on vaccinations and preventatives. Our adoption process includes references and background checks, a vet check and a home visit.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Angel is super playful and loves to do somersaults and is a great lap cat, too.

Her coloring is a rich blue gray color with pale orange dappling of Tortoiseshell.  Her blue and cream coloring is velvety and soft.  

Gigi is Angel’s mom and the two are best friends and it would be lovely for them to be adopted together. But, they could be adopted separately as well.  

Angel is not an alpha and can be the cat who is chased by others who are bullies. She will depend greatly on her humans for love.

She is a lot of fun and actually is more intelligent than most cats 

Angel is Gigi’s daughter, born in May 2013.

Visit our website at: www.animalnetwork.org to see our fees, adoption requirements and to view other available animals we have for adoption. Email: contact@animalnetwork.org for the application to adopt and tell us a little about your family’s lifestyle and home. Some of the new arrivals can be seen in the caregiver’s homes on weekdays. A mandatory pet parenting class is given on Saturdays so you can learn how to introduce your new pet to existing ones, teaching house manners, recommended foods and the best litter, and what you can do to avoid your cat from getting certain diseases. If you can’t find the pet that you are looking for sign up for our “Pet Match Service” and tell us what you are looking for. A $25 donation is accepted for this 1 year service.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
• DOB:  08/10/14
  • Requires another dog in home: Yes
  • Okay with dogs of all sizes: Yes, has only been around small dogs
  • Okay with cats: Yes, needs slow intro
  • Okay with children under 12 years old: Unknown

  • Requires a fenced yard:   No, but please continue working on leash training

Hello, my name is Moka, and I am an adult female! I am a Shiba/Shar Pei/French Bulldog mix who loves to lay in the warm sun, chew on my doggy toys, and go on walks/hikes. My most favoritest treat is Old Mother Hubbard’s Peanut Butter Biscuits (yum!!) I am a very happy and playful girl who will always be excited to see you, no matter how long you’ve been away. I am good with cats (I live with three of them!) and dogs of all sizes. I love being a part of the pack. I am a good fit for a family of any size, and I get along very well with young kids. 

I am potty-trained and I do very well on walks - so I don’t need a fenced yard to play in so long as I get my exercise. I am very smart and I am always doing my best to make you happy, whether I am licking your toes or being a very good girl with my many known obedience commands. I am also crate-trained, but it’s not where I prefer to spend my time (and why would it be when I could be playing with you!) Foster mom says that they did not have to train me out of any bad behaviors when they got me. She says I am a loyal, house-trained, happy dog. I just want everyone to see my goofy smile and fall in love with me! I hope you’ve fallen in love with me, too, so we can start playing together very soon. Love, Moka

Some of our dogs are obtained from commercial breeders where they spent their lives getting comfort from their canine friends. Others have come from various situations where they are lacking confidence in humans. In turn, most require another companion dog in their forever home in order for them to feel safe. If you are interested in a particular dog, and do not currently have a dog residing with you, please understand that your home might not be the right fit for many of our dogs.

 
 

***Be sure to check your spam/junk folder as sometimes our emails end up there***

I am all healed up and would love home with understanding people. I would do best in a quiet home with my few people that understand and love me. I will need on going care for my skin so I don't get sores. The volunteers keep my skin nice and moisturized and away from the sun so I don't get sun burns. I know lots of commands, sit, down, shake and I am crate trained. I love to play with toys too! I like playing with other dogs but I need a home with no kids.  Everyone says I am a very handsome boy. 

If you are interested in Barclay we ask you to become a volunteer at the Last Hope Adoption Center so he can get to know you! Barclay has stranger danger and takes time to warm up to new people.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
"Won't you please pay attention to me? I just want to play!"

Meet Prince, an active 10 year old Black Labrador Retriever / English Pointer mix. Poor Prince was confined to an apartment with no socialization and little attention because the family lost interest in him. LDDR agreed to take Prince and find the right home for him. He is now receiving lots of playtime and TLC in his foster home while waiting for a forever home.

Prince is your typical busy dog that will do best in a home with an adopter who is willing to work with him to teach him some proper manners. He can be a bit wary of unknown people and would need slow introductions to someone he doesn't know. A fenced yard would be ideal to play ball, as that’s his favorite thing to do. Prince walks well on a leash except when a car goes by. He currently has a desire to chase moving cars. He is perfectly house trained and will bark at the door to let you know he needs to go out, and he will bark at the door to come back in, too. Prince is ok with most dogs when properly introduced, but he will grumble if a dog gets too chummy or rude.

For more information or questions, email Tim at tmb611@msn.com.

BREED/COLORING: Chihuahua Mix/ Cream Coloring

SIZE: Chuck is about 13 lbs and is full grown

HISTORY: Chuck was found running scared in an industrial area in the San Fernando Valley. We believe Chuck was originally thrown out on the streets to fend for himself by his previous owner.

PERSONALITY: Chuck seems shy at first but once he is comfortable he is a waggy kissy little guy. He wants to be a lap dog completely if he can.

TRAINING: Chuck has not had much in the ways of training, so he will require some patience.

WOULD DO BEST: Chuck would do great in almost any type of home.

CATS/DOGS/KIDS: Chuck is good with cats & dogs. We do not recommend chuck for a home with small children unless there is already a small dog there because he is shy and might shy away from them.

Blossom has not liked having girl friends but loves her male doggy friends. She absolutely loves people too! If you are looking for a big dog personality in a small package, Blossom is the dog for you. Could you be her people that she's waited so long for? If you are interested in adopting her, please visit iwag.org to fill out an adoption application.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Are you a telecommuter in search of a lap warmer? This affectionate and well-behaved brown tabby seeks a laid back companion(s) to keep company. He promises to be well behaved during your Zoom meetings as long as you keep rubbing his ears and scratching his chin.

Circles is a real survivor who never let life's challenges ruin his delightfully sunny personality. As a kitten, he was found circling and dazed in the the middle of a road by a concerned motorist, who brought him to an area vet. He had likely been hit by a car and suffered a head injury. He has a permanent mild head tilt and a kinked tail from being broken in a couple places, as well as some slight vision and hearing impairments. He can hear louder noises and louder voices, and we believe only one of his eyes is sight impaired. He has adapted well to all of these challenges. He can climb a cat tree, jump up in your lap, go up and down stairs, eat, drink, and use a litter box like any normal cat. He got his name because he will "circle" around several times when he is happy to see you. He is just adorable.

Circles was adopted and returned to Last Hope when his former family had extenuating circumstances and could no longer care for him. He is now back with his former foster family, who were delighted to see him again!

Circles also gives hugs: he will sit on your lap, put his paws on your shoulders, and rub your chin all day long if he can get you to sit still long enough! He gets along with other cats and kittens (after proper introduction) young and old. He is OK with children as long as they are gentle with him. Older children would be preferred to younger ones. He has some mild balance issues (due to his head tilt), so he needs to be picked up and set down gently when handled so he doesn't lose his balance. He also does well with mellow cat-savvy dogs.

Circles has a heart of gold and is looking for that special human who will see he is the "purrfect" cat despite the fact he is slightly "differently-abled." More importantly, after being surrendered by his beloved family of 5 years, he needs a calm, stable home who will never break his heart again.

Circles is neutered, microchipped, and up to date on vaccinations. Circles must be a strictly indoor cat as he has limited abilities and would not be able to outrun or defend himself from predators, including at-large dogs.

If you are interested in learning more about Circles from his foster parents, please complete a no-obligation adoption application on our website.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
When Jeri and Meri were found, they were essentially feral. They were hiding under a shipping container they had adopted as their home. It is unknown how long they were living there, as the property was only visited by the owners sporadically. When the landowners found them, it took quite a while to coax them out into the open where they were eventually trapped. Both were very skinny, dehydrated and terrified of people. And both are still very wary and untrusting of new people and new situations.  On occasion, both dogs still nip their rescuers when they are stressed or excited.  This is not to say that they would not warm up to other people.  But it will take a "dog-savvy" person with great patience, love and a very calm, low activity home. Once the level of trust is earned, either Jeri or Meri would be a sweet companion and friend. 

Meri and Jeri will NOT be good with seniors, children or cats because of their unpredictability and their terrier tendencies. They should probably be adopted separately in order to fully bond with the new owner(s).

Jeri is neutered, vaccinated and on Heartworm preventative. Meri is spayed, vaccinated, and on Heartworm preventative. You can speak to his foster parents to learn more by calling 662-342-9448 or emailing: info@desotoanimalrescue.org

attributes.descriptionHtml:
"Maude is a super - affectionate people pleaser! 

Maude loves playing fetch, but is not aware of how strong she is. She would do best in a home with no small children and where she could be the only fur baby...she put in a request for sleeping in the bed!

She is crate-trained and housebroken, and responds well to firm and consistent verbal commands. She knows how to sit, stay, and lay down, and walks well on a leash once she gets over her initial excitement. "

Maude even high-fives and rolls over for dinner. *See the video here on her profile!*

Maude would be a great jogging companion for an active person, and will even cuddle after a workout. Some of Maude's "energy and excitement" may be from being in a home with too many other dogs, as foster care is just a life-saving situation at times, not an ideal one.  With that said, we are likely not seeing Maude's highest potential as a canine companion.

Maude is current on vaccinations, spayed, and microchipped. Current on heartworm preventative and flea preventative. 

If you are interested in Maude, please fill out a  Dog Adoption Application

Our adoptions include a foster period of 4-6 weeks so that you can be sure that this pet is a good fit without any pressure, and we are available to answer any behavior or training questions during that time (and beyond, if you wish).

**Local adoptions preferred (within 1-2 hrs of the Greater New Orleans area), but please contact us if you live outside of this area, as exceptions are sometimes made on an individual basis depending on the dog or circumstances. We do not ship animals, as a part of our adoption process is for the potential adopter(s) to meet the dog to assess if he/she is a match for the family.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Quick Facts:

Breed(s): Domestic Shorthair
Gender: Neutered Male
Age: 6 years
I’m good with: 
Dogs? No    
Cats? Yes - Mellow non-dominant cats    
Kids? No 

History:
Vander was brought to the Hermitage by a very caring case worker when he was just 6 months old in December of 2014 after a 6 year old cut of his ear with a pair of scissors.

Personality:
Vander is a spunky ball of energy! Everyone here at the shelter loves his goofy antics and adorably derpy personality. He loves escaping into the various different rooms at the shelter to explore and find new things to play with. Vander is a staff and volunteer favorite here and we would love to see him find his very own forever people despite how bittersweet it would be. Due to his past trauma Vander isn't the biggest fan of kids and will often hid when he sees them so he would do best in a adult or teenager only home. He can get a bit overstimulated at times during play and pets and can nip a little bit. Vander will need a very understanding, patient, cat savvy adopter who understands and respects his behavioral quirks. 

Medical: 
Vander has a history of inappropriate urination, this is a behavioral problem he has had for most of his time with us.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
They call me Leon. I’m a good-looking Redbone, 9 years old and 44lbs, with big soulful eyes (so I’m told) who’s just looking for someone to love me in a long-term relationship. You see, when I love, I love completely but I need some time to get to know you. Can you give me some of your time? I promise to make it worth your while.

I live at EHR’s kennel but one day a week my best friend brings me to his house to hang with him and his family. Those are the best days because I get to run & run & just stretch out my long legs. It just feels so good. And I have a canine buddy who runs & plays with me, too, along with a couple of teenaged boys. I mean, those are the happiest hours of my week. And they’ve helped me learn good house manners so when you find me – and I sure hope you do – you will be impressed by what a good dog I am.

I’m housetrained and I don’t jump up on the furniture – I’ve even completed a dog obedience class. I have lots of energy and I love to play with toys. I’m a good listener and I’m eager to please – all I want to do is make you happy.  I’ve worked hard to become the dog I am today with a lot of help from my friends.

I hope you’ll give me the chance to prove that I’m the right dog for you. Go to www.ehrdogs.org and fill out an application to adopt (or to foster if you’d just like to take things slow with me) and be sure to mention my name – LEON! I’ll be waiting at the kennel, patiently, hopefully, for you to find me & bring me home.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
My name is Skittles and my foster mom found me abandoned in a HEB parking lot one day.  She asked around and people had been feeding me for a couple of years!  Once she caught me, she found out I ws microchipped, but when she located my owners, they had moved...and had left me behind.  So, being a cat, I found my way to HEB and relied on kind humans to feed me.  It took a while for me to trust my foster mom, and I'm still jump if you try to pet me too quickly.  Apparently, I wasn't treated all that great.

Anyways, I think I'm ready to trust another human now.  I do get along with cats, but little children would probably make me nervous.  And my foster mom doesn't know about dogs since we don't have any here.  It'd be great if I could have my own family again, but I might take some tender, loving care at first.  Through my foster family, I've found out humans can be good....and a forever home would be awesome!

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hi, my name is Jossie and I'm about 6 1/2 years old.  Me and my litter mates were surrendered to Bond County Humane Society for adoption because the people we lived with did not want us.  I am sociable and playful.  Before I came to live at BCHS I lived in a garage but I was not well socialized with people and played with an 8 year old.  I don't have any experience with dogs.  I like to play with toys, string, boxes or pretty much anything.  In 2017 I was diagnosed with IBD (Inflammatory Bowel Disease).  In my case it affects my stomach, not my intestines.  Because my stomach is involved it causes me to have chronic vomiting.  My care for this condition includes food that I can tolerate.  In my case it's food with fish, not any meat.  The other part of my care is supplemental injections under the skin of  B-12.  This is needed because my body is unable to absorb this vitamin.   I have done well on the maintenance program described.  I have been able to maintain a healthy weight and I am not prone to vomiting.  I am spayed, UTD on vaccinations, tested for FeLV/FIV, treated for internal and external parasites and microchipped. My adoption fee is by donation. If you are interested in adopting me please complete an adoption profile in person or on-line at www.bondcohs.petfinder.com.  Email the completed profile to the address provided.    A copy of our policy regarding warranties, refunds or returns is available upon request.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Meet Leo!

On a cold day in March of 2014 a Good Samaritan stopped their car on the side of a highway and opened their side door. In jumped a scared, skinny and exhausted stray who was relieved to be away from the dangers of the highway. His rescuer didn’t know what this dog had been through or how long he had been out on his own, but she could tell he hadn’t been treated kindly. She brought him to the vet where she found he was only 8 months old, very underweight, but still sweet and affectionate with everyone he met. She decided to name this resilient soul a courageous name that would fit his spirit, and settled on “Leo.”

When Leo arrived at Adopt-A-Dog just a few days later he became an immediate staff favorite. Everyone was amazed by how smart he was and how fast he learned new things and we were sure he would be adopted quickly. No one could have predicted that six YEARS later, Leo would still be with us, now as our longest resident at the shelter.

Six years is a long and exhausting time for a shelter dog, but for Leo he has taken it all in stride. After all, our shelter may be the nicest place he has ever been able to call “home.” In his time with us he has remained a staff and volunteer favorite, aced his obedience training, and even gone on some adventures! He loves to swim, go for long car rides, and go jogging or hiking with a pal.
This sweet, athletic, intelligent, handsome, incredible dog has been waiting so long for a home and no dog is more deserving, since Leo may never have had a place to call home in his whole life. Let’s make 2021 the year that he finally finds a soft place to lay his head and truly relax.


The first step to adopting one of our dogs is to fill out our online adoptions questionnaire located here: https://forms.gle/5heEH8S6c7zXBneD7

On a cold day in March of 2014 a Good Samaritan stopped their car on the side of a highway and opened their side door. In jumped a scared, skinny and exhausted stray who was relieved to be away from the dangers of the highway. His rescuer didn’t know what this dog had been through or how long he had been out on his own, but she could tell he hadn’t been treated kindly. She brought him to the vet where she found he was only 8 months old, very underweight, but still sweet and affectionate with everyone he met. She decided to name this resilient soul a courageous name that would fit his spirit, and settled on “Leo.”

When Leo arrived at Adopt-A-Dog just a few days later he became an immediate staff favorite. Everyone was amazed by how smart he was and how fast he learned new things and we were sure he would be adopted quickly. No one could have predicted that six YEARS later, Leo would still be with us, now as our longest resident at the shelter.

Six years is a long and exhausting time for a shelter dog, but for Leo he has taken it all in stride. After all, our shelter may be the nicest place he has ever been able to call “home.” In his time with us he has remained a staff and volunteer favorite, aced his obedience training, and even gone on some adventures! He loves to swim, go for long car rides, and go jogging or hiking with a pal.
This sweet, athletic, intelligent, handsome, incredible dog has been waiting so long for a home and no dog is more deserving, since Leo may never have had a place to call home in his whole life. Let’s make 2021 the year that he finally finds a soft place to lay his head and truly relax.


The first step to adopting one of our dogs is to fill out our online adoptions questionnaire located here: https://forms.gle/5heEH8S6c7zXBneD7

attributes.descriptionHtml: Pennie Dalila is a 6 year old dachshund mix. She came into our rescue from a loving home but went down in her back and the family knew they couldn't take care of all her needs. Pennie is now in our care and with some strict crate rest and medications has regained function of her back legs! The vet discovered that she does have arthritis so is now taking a daily supplement. She had been doing some home therapy but occasional walks seem to be all she needs to keep her leg muscles nice and strong. She wants to greet every human and dog she meets so these walks are her favorite time of day. With how friendly she is, she also loves accompanying her foster parents to all the dog friendly spots in town. Pennie truly just wants to be the center of attention. Her ideal family would give her belly and head rubs 24/7 but she understands you get busy so she can also keep herself busy by playing with her favorite toy, a piece of cloth. Since she is still recovering, she would do best in a quiet home where she's not tempted to play too hard and rehurt herself. She is still technically disabled but we have found ways to work with her to have a great life. If you would like to give her a chance, feel free to put in a request and her foster mom would love to talk to you to see if you are the right family for her. This pup is a spunky little girl that is just looking for a family to love her like the princess she is. If you're looking for a best friend or shadow, Pennie is your girl.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Meet Winston!
Winston has been through a lot in his life and is so deserving of a forever home! We found Winston at a local municipal shelter where he had been living for months. He rarely got out of his kennel, and was not socialized with many new people. We decided to bring him to our shelter to try to give him a better quality of life while he waits for his perfect home to come along.

Winston is incredibly loyal and loving to people he trusts, but it takes some time for him to build trust with a new person. He is definitely worth the effort because once he loves someone it is for life! There is nothing this boy loves more than to sit at the feet of his person and just relax in their presence.

Winnie has been through strict obedience training and has excelled in the routine of training. He also thoroughly enjoys agility training and taking long walks. Whoever adopts this boy will need to have the dedication to commit to bonding with him and continuing his training so he can be the best dog he can be for the rest of his long and happy life. In a perfect world, he be the only pet in an adult only home, but he does have the potential to live with another easy-going female dog.

The first step to adopting one of our dogs is to fill out our online adoptions questionnaire located here: https://forms.gle/5heEH8S6c7zXBneD7

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Banjo would love to find his forever home!  He loves everyone he meets, but being a smaller breed dog warms up a little slower to dog friends.  He gets along great with his foster moms Boxer.  Just a little time and patience as with any dog moving into a new home!  He would also be fine as an only dog or with cats.

He makes us laugh with his talking!  It almost sounds like a growl, but he will come talk to us when he wants to go outside or when he thinks its dinner time. :)  He knows lots of commands (sit, wait, outside, in the house, and can do a few tricks too)  He gets the zoomies every once in a while which is so cute to watch and settles down nicely and gets comfortable on a dog bed or next to you on the couch or bed if you let him.  (oh yeah.....he's got a cute little snore too)

Since coming into his foster home, Banjo has been more active and lost a couple needed pounds.  He loves to go on walks and does awesome on a leash.  A few more pounds and he will be at his ideal weight!

He is such a sweet dog and I hope you consider him for part of your family.  Being an adult dog already is also great as he doesn't chew on anything, is housetrained and knows commands....he will just need to learn your routine! :)  GREAT LITTLE COMPANION!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Happy has been in and out of several homes since he was a tiny puppy. His first owner listed him on Craigslist. His third owner found him wearing the second owner's ID tags, but when contacted they said they did not want him anymore. Happy was surrendered to Emmy's Hope Rescue in January 2015.  His third / last family was moving out of the country and could not take him.

Happy came to Emmy's Hope heartworm positive. He has gone through the treatment and was cured of heartworms. :))  Happy is good with cats and he likes to run and play outside with other little dogs his size. When playtime is over and he is called inside, he comes right away. He is very good about going back inside his kennel, in fact he considers it his safety zone. Happy enjoys being petted but does not really like to sit in your lap, he prefers sitting beside you. He will snap at young children, they make him very nervous. Little Happy has been waiting a long time to find his special family, the one that will love and keep him forever this time.

Estimated birthdate - Jan. 2013.

Estimated weight - 10 lbs.

If you would like to meet Happy, please call or text Stephanie at: 281-622-6549.

*** ADOPTION  CRITERIA ***

To qualify to adopt from Emmy's Hope Rescue,

YOU MUST HAVE ALL 4 QUALIFIERS:

1. Live in the Houston area (no more than an hour's drive away).

2. Be 21 years or older.

3. Have a fenced yard. Fencing must touch the ground all the way around the yard.

4. We are looking for experienced pet owners. You must  have at least 2-3 years of good vet history, with your current and / or past dogs. Your vet record should show that you take your dog(s) to the vet annually for an exam and to update their Rabies and DHPP (distemper, parvo) vaccinations and heartworm testing, and that you purchase a monthly heartworm preventative.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hi, I’m Duke! I am a charming, happy, Cattle Dog mix, about 6-7 yrs old.  I love to go for walks  or runs  (and I am really good at it!). I also love car rides, stuffed animals, and playing in a fenced-in backyard. I am completely house trained,  crate trained ,  and am very intelligent. I know what sit,  lay down , and stay mean, but I could use some more training to work on those commands and anything else you want to teach me.  I love to run and play; I have a whole lot of energy, but I also love to cuddle, give kisses and be loved by my human companion .  Basically, I just like to be doing what my people are.   I am very cautious of new people. I really prefer to come check you out first, and I really rather you don’t pet me until I know you will treat me with kindness.  I may  have to meet you a couple times before  I know I can trust you .   I can’t tell my friends at Last Hope what happened to me before I came to stay with them, but all they know is that it takes me a while to trust people and be comfortable in situations.  Because of this, I should not be in a home with young kids or teens.  My dream home would be with an adult family who is familiar with my kind of challenges and who has a physically fenced in yard. I also want 1 other playful dog around my size (50 pounds+) or bigger  to play with (I can play a little rough so they need to be tough like me) and a family who is very patient with me while I adjust to new people in my life.  I am a very loyal companion and I just want to please my humans!   Once I know I can trust you, I just want to be around you and will be your shadow as you go through your day.  I have also had my DNA tested! I am officially an Australian Cattle Dog/Harrier mix!   

Last Hope requires that all pets be kept as indoor pets, be altered and current on vaccinations and preventatives. Our adoption process includes reference and vet checks and a home visit. The adoption fee includes: spay/neuter, microchip and vaccinations.

Boots and Tipper were just little puppies when they were rescued from the middle of a busy road in Magnolia. They came to Emmy's Hope Rescue in February 2014. Sadly, after all this time, they have never been adopted and had their own family. 

Boots and Tipper have grown into big handsome guys. They love to run, chase and wrestle with each other. If there is water, they will happily play in it. If there is a pond, Tipper likes to swim. Boots likes to play fetch.. They both enjoy being petted and Boots will try to climb in your lap and cuddle.

For someone wanting two dogs, please consider adopting both Boots and his brother, Tipper  They enjoy each other's company and would love to stay together!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
DOB: August, 2009

BREED/COLORING: Pitbull Mix; blue and white

SIZE: Astro is approximately 70lbs and is full grown.

HISTORY: Astro was originally rescued from the shelter where he was turned in as an owner surrender. Unfortunately the rescue who was caring for Astro is no more, and so he entered into our care.

TRAINING: Astro may require some training in a new environment. 

WOULD DO BEST: Astro would do best in a home with a family that is Pit-savvy and willing to give him stuff to do to keep busy (walks, training, playing, etc). Astro will require a yard. He could be with another calm, non-Alpha large male dog... but he would prefer to have a yard and family to himself.

CATS/DOGS/KIDS: Astro is not a dog park dog and needs a handler that understands that he can be defensive on leash. He could be with another large male dog that shows no Alpha signs. No cats for him. He has met kids of all ages and has been sweet with everyone.

VET RECORD: All of our dogs are currently vaccinated, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption.

AVAILABILITY: This dog is available for adoption now and is being fostered or kenneled in the San Fernando Valley area. Please email us and we will send you an adoption application. Local adoptions only (we do not ship dogs).

Visit our website: http://www.foreverhomepetrescue.org/

VET RECORD: All of our dogs are currently vaccinated, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption.





AVAILABILITY: This dog is available for adoption now and is being fostered or kenneled in the San Fernando Valley area. Please email us and we will send you an adoption application. Local adoptions only (we do not ship dogs).





Visit our website: http://www.foreverhomepetrescue.org/

attributes.descriptionHtml:
I was surrendered to the pound by my family, which was a pretty devastating experience for me. I am very affectionate and attach very quickly to every person I meet. I do get attached so much that I don’t want to share you with somebody else and therefore, I may become protective. So, my foster mum tells me that I need a person who can be my leader, who will show me the way and help me to trust again. I am very smart and eager to learn. I am also great with dogs and I would just love it if I could live with a canine companion and have a yard to romp around in. I really don't need too much; just a new forever home — is yours available?

If you are interested in meeting Jack Black, please download the Adoption Questionnaire, fill it out and email it back to us at info@farescue.org or fax (310) 362-0321. You can also meet this and/or other available dogs at our weekend adoptions.

[Jack Black weighs 45 lbs.]

attributes.descriptionHtml: I am Grayson and I’ve been in rescue quite some time. I am a sweet boy. My perfect home would be an experienced female owner versus a first time owner. I would really like a fenced yard to run and play in and also someone who takes me for walks or on some adventures. I adore trails and stuff but am not a huge fan of swimming.    If you can help me I know I can be a very good boy and will become your best friend too.   Grayson is a beautiful pittie/pointer, male with green eyes. He will melt your heart. He has been at Castoff way too long. Grayson would make a fabulous companion for any woman. He loves the ladies. He is the type of dog that shows total loyalty and protection. Grayson needs a fenced hard so he can run. He loves attention, loves to run and play but is not great with other animals. In his past he has been abused and thankfully he came to Castoff. This is why we are looking for a female that would love a great watchdog and a forever companion. attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hello,

My name is Addison, kind of a sophisticated English name. I like it.  

I just got here from the Bastrop shelter with my sister Artemis and we were scared out of our wits.  I have gotten a lot more comfortable BUT my sister is still more afraid than I am.

Foster mom will be keeping us for a week or two more or until we are comfortable being handled and with people but we will be looking for our special forever home the whole time!

Let my foster mom know you might want me as your BFF and then come to meet me!!!

ADDISON UPDATE:
Wow, time flies when you're having fun.  Foster Mom had to be away for 3 months and we did not get much attention while she was gone, but now we're having special "lessons" in liking people and we're doing quite well.  My sister is STILL a big scaredy cat, but Foster Mom and Foster Sister are going to work really hard with her during Christmas vacation so we will be ready for our forever homes soon after.  We are both very healthy and beautiful and we are the age shown below here on this page.  We will make great BFF's, why not ask about us and take a chance - you won't be sorry!

ADDISON UPDATE Jan 16:  We are still VERY skittery and Mom is going to order some Jackson Galaxy flower remedies and we will be moved into large cages so Mom and Sis can work directly with each one of us.  Here's hoping - -

FOSTER MOM UPDATE March 13:  Happy to say that Addison is doing very well.  Still a bit timid, but coming up to be petted and enjoying it.  She's out of a cage and lots of the "roaming" kitties in the house have been allowed into the room where she is and it's now on to the next step - allowing her to come out of the kitty room and into the normal house if she wants. 

I've changed her status to "available for adoption" and she is ready for a home that is fairly quiet with someone who is willing to be gentle and patient with her.  She's a really SWEET kitty and deserves a chance at a forever home.  She gets along with other kitties, so a home with another buddy would be great.

ADDISON UPDATE September 10, 2016: I am sooo ready for love <G>.  Addison is finally ready fully for a home.  She will take a bit to get used to the new digs, but she's been off with a temp foster for 6 weeks, is back and is asking to be petted, venturing out in the house and has left sister behind in so many ways.  She can be picked up, petted and will most of the time come to you.  Loud or sudden movements still un-nerve her, but in a normal home setting she'll be a great companion.  Addison is very healthy and up to date on vaccinations and is spayed and microchipped!  Won't you consider HER as your new BFF?

ADDISON UPDATE: October 2018:  Hey, I'm back.  Had a little health scare but turns out it was a wrong diagnosis and I'm healthy as can be.  I've been living in foster mom's bedroom and having a lot of fun and attention.  I love to sleep right next to her leg and I love being petted and I even beg to be petted.  I am still a little insecure and it shows when you move fast or try to chase or catch me.  I'm also a bit face shy still although I love it when you scratch and pet my head, just nervous if you try to use two hands at once.  If I'm on the bed and I know you, you can pick me up.  I will be okay for a few minutes but after that I want down.  I have the tiniest little meow, you'd think I was a kitten.  I might be a little bit insecure still BUT once I settle in and get to know you I'll be your BFF and give you back lots of love!

New pics coming soon!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Tabitha was born about April 1, 2013 and weighs a bit too much at about 90 lbs.  This girl is very proud of her curves and when her favorite human has been gone for a few hours she does the most delightful, bouncy, dance that we've ever seen!   She is absolutely adorable and has been very good with all of us, but terribly shy at first.  She is good with other dogs, fine in the car and on leash.  This gorgeous girl has been tossed away and will be so thankful for a new home where she will be cherished!  She was left at a shelter when her babies were two days old, guess she became an inconvenience.  She was terrified for herself and her infants when we loaded them up to come here just a couple of days later.  She was a very good Mom, surmounted the stress and kept taking care of her babies who grew to be strong and healthy and now she is looking for a new home that will love her unconditionally!  It is obvious that Tabitha has not always been treated well by humans and she is terrified of being touched by new humans and she is terrified of new places.  She will take much time and effort to adjust to a new life, but she is a really wonderful, loving, girl once comfortable.  Due to her fears she truly must have a fenced in yard. Tabitha is too interested in cats to live with any.
Adoptions fees vary based on adoptability. In general our fees include spay/neuter, all age appropriate vaccines, Home Again micro-chipping & registration, worming & flea control - a "complete" pet.
Joyful Rescues has no funding except for our adoption fees and miscellaneous donations. Pet care and vet bills are expensive - you must be ready to take on this financial (as well as emotional) responsibility.

YOU MUST BE AT LEAST 25 YEARS OF AGE TO ADOPT A DOG FROM JOYFUL RESCUES
 
We keep our pet list as up-to-date as possible. As soon as a pet is adopted, it is removed from the list. If a pet is still showing, it is still available for adoption.
 
Can't Adopt Me?  SPONSOR ME
Look for the Link "Special Instructions to Seller" if you want to note a particular pet

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Do you like big cuddly bears? Then I am the dog for you! My name is Meya and I am a 7 year old, 60 pound Staffordshire, Husky and Chow mix who loves to climb into your lap and relax with you. I also love to go for walks and play fetch. I walk well on leash and I am great at bringing the ball back during games of fetch. I have learned the commands sit, down, off, out, and stay, but I am still working on drop and leave it. I am pretty easy to train because I love treats! I also love to be with my people and am happiest when I have them all to myself. I adore older kids and love to give kisses. I have been trained to sleep in a crate at night, but if you will let me I would love to sleep cuddled up with you. But, I prefer to be the only pet in your life; cats are definitely not for me. If you know my breed and are looking for a forever friend, look no further than me Meya!

If you are interested in adopting, please go to our website and complete the adoption application: http://www.icaredogrescue.org/ready-to-adopt/

Adoption fee includes: spay/neuter • shots up to date • micro-chip • fecal and vet check

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Copper was found wandering in a Houston apartment complex. He was wearing a collar and a tag with his name and a phone number. Unfortunately the phone was disconnected and he could not be reunited with his family. Copper was taken in by Emmy's Hope Rescue in 2014.

Copper has an under bite with protruding teeth that makes him look like he is always smiling. He enjoys running and playing with his canine buddies, he's friendly with cats and he likes cuddling with his favorite humans.

Approximate birth date: December 2013. 

Estimated weight: 25 lbs.

If you would like to meet Copper, please call or text Stephanie at: 281-622-6549.

*** ADOPTION  CRITERIA ***

To qualify to adopt from Emmy's Hope Rescue,

YOU MUST HAVE ALL 4 QUALIFIERS:

1. Live in the Houston area (no more than an hour's drive away).

2. Be 21 years or older.

3. Have a fenced yard. Fencing must touch the ground all the way around the yard.

4. We are looking for experienced pet owners. You must  have at least 2-3 years of good vet history, with your current and / or past dogs. Your vet record should show that you take your dog(s) to the vet annually for an exam and to update their Rabies and DHPP (distemper, parvo) vaccinations and heartworm testing, and that you purchase a monthly heartworm preventative.
attributes.name: Copper

attributes.descriptionHtml:
DOB 7/2014

TC is a tortie point Siamese mix.

She was left behind in a shopping center parking lot, in a cage. 

We don't know if she's weird because this happened to her, or vice-versa. She's a very, VERY strange cat.

She likes to be petted - on her terms. She will shriek at times, or roll over for tummy rubs - or both. She likes to help with working from home, and our current state of social distancing is currently very pleasing to TC. She will hang out with you, charging full speed at your lap, and then will LEAP into the air, and land with a big heavy thud, and settle in for some reading or working or TV time. She likes to be petted, and when she's had enough she will emit a chilling halloween kitty shriek that will keep your neighbors away. Which is good; social distancing, remember?

Because of her eccentric nature, TC definitely needs an experienced cat parent. She is tolerant of dogs, maybe even likes them a little bit. She would be totally indifferent to other cats (I would say she needs to be an only cat, but she does need someone to keep her attitude in check and also to help her exercise by chasing her around the house). 

If you are looking for a buddy to keep you home and on the couch, TC is your girl!

 

**** PLEASE NOTE THAT TC IS NOT A GOOD STARTER CAT****
attributes.name: TC

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hi, my name is Kiwi!  I love kisses, playing tug of war, snuggling, and taking long naps in my humans lap (although i'll nap in my crate if a human lap isn't available).   I also love playing with toys, any toys, all toys, yay toys!  My  favorite thing in the whole world is car rides, though!  It doesn't matter where we're going, as long as I can ride in the car with you!  

I am crate trained and house trained! I'd do best without small children because I have a big puppy personality so I'm  still learning to keep all 4 paws on the ground when I get too excited. Even though I am a very hyper puppy, that also means I am a great running buddy! I need a little help with leash manners, but trust me I'll run with you as long as you want if you'll have some patience!!

I've been in rescue since I was a little puppy. I was found in the middle of the street with my brother, and I was so sick and unhealthy that I had almost no hair! I grew up with a lot of anxiety because of this but in my 2 years in rescue I've gotten a lot of training to help with my anxiety. I still need a close eye on me with other dogs when I'm in my house, so I would be best in a single dog home, but I promise to do my ABSOLUTE BEST to be on my best behavior if you have some patience and love for me! 

I can't wait to meet my forever family, who I will love more than ANYTHING!! Please give me a chance to show you that I can be the best companion ever! Will you give me a shot??

Please contact   app@aarfhouston.org  for more information about this dog.  You can apply online by clicking on  Application   . Once your application is approved, we will schedule a meet and greet at one of our adoption events.  Thank you for considering a rescue!

attributes.descriptionHtml: My name is Chuck. I'm going about my day trying to figure out where I'm going to get my next meal. I'm not paying attention and BAM, I was hit by a car. How I came out of that brush with death with just scrapes and bruises I will never know. I certainly am happy that I lived to tell about it though! I am on the quiet side and a little shy, but I'm not scared and hiding. I enjoy human, as well as feline, companionship. It may take me a little bit to warm up, but once I do I'm a lovey guy. I am sure to become a more confident and outgoing kitty with a little time and patience. Will you be that lucky person to share my new lease on life?

DOB: November 26th 2013

BREED/COLORING: Shihtzu/Terrier Mix; White & Brown

SIZE: Toby is 13lbs and is full grown.

HISTORY: Toby was owner surrendered to us because his family lost their home and were forced to move.

PERSONALITY: Toby is shy, he is takes a minute to get to know you - but once he does he comes up to you and leans on you for some scritches. He is very sweet and goofy when he's comfortable.

TRAINING: Toby has had no prior training to our knowledge. His crate training is going well.

WOULD DO BEST: Toby would do best with another dog, and someone who can handle his first couple moments of shyness.  

CATS/DOGS/KIDS: Toby is good with other dogs, and okay with cats. We would not recommend him for kids under 10.

Vet Record: All of our dogs are currently vaccinated, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Max is available through our Homebuddies program. He is very specific about the dogs he likes, so if you have another dog, they would need to come to the visit to make sure they get a long. He is located at our Temple, Ga adoption center. 

 

DOB: 2014 

Health: Healthy 

Behavior: Fun, energetic

Playfulness: Very  

Affectionate: Can be, loves his back scratched and butt pats   

Calm: Not often 

High Energy: Yes 

Dog Friendly: Yes, gets along with females and calm non-dominant males.  

Cat Friendly: No  

Toddler/Baby Appropriate: No

Child Appropriate: Yes, Older  

Good for first time dog owners: Yes, be advised I can be fearful of Strangers, but I have gotten much better! 

Fetches: Yes 

Swims: No   

Other: Absolutely loves to fetch, can be dog selective. Very fun and energetic

My name is Max!

Hey, is that a ball?! Oh, please throw that ball! I promise to bring it back and set it at your feet so you can throw it again and we can play for hours outside! I will be your best friend! IWAG taught me to how to drop the ball so I can chase it more! And boy, do I love it! IWAG rescued me because I was living in a small home where I couldn’t get enough exercise. Now I can run around and be myself!

I am VERY energetic and I would love a large area for me to run around in. I am very loving to all people and.  I would cuddle beside you all night and run outside with you all day. I’m ready to find my forever home! I love it here but I am ready to be with my family to love unconditionally! I get along with most dogs, both male and female. I would love to have a non-dominate male that I can hang with and a female dog who I can play with all day! 

Please come and visit me! I have been at IWAG all my life! I promise to be a good boy and love on you with my kisses. I can’t wait to see you! I’m excited just thinking about it!

Love, Max

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Big sweet handsome Oreo was dumped in a rural neighborhood and left to fend for himself.  Just a big baby when first rescued by Emmy's Hope, Oreo weighed about 50 lbs.      But he continued to grow over the next year! 

Oreo is very friendly, like a big lovable teddy bear with people. He loves to wrestle and play with other big dogs. Oreo would be great with older kids and would definitely enjoy a large yard to run in.

Estimated birthdate: July 2014   

Approximate weight: 90 lbs.

If you would like to meet Oreo, please call or text Stephanie at 281-622-6549.

*** ADOPTION  CRITERIA ***

To qualify to adopt from Emmy's Hope Rescue,

YOU MUST HAVE ALL 4 QUALIFIERS:

1. Live in the Houston area (no more than an hour's drive away).

2. Be 21 years or older.

3. Have a fenced yard. Fencing must touch the ground all the way around the yard.

4. We are looking for experienced pet owners. You must  have at least 2-3 years of good vet history, with your current and / or past dogs. Your vet record should show that you take your dog(s) to the vet annually for an exam and to update their Rabies and DHPP (distemper, parvo) vaccinations and heartworm testing, and that you purchase a monthly heartworm preventative.

DOB: September 2012

BREED/COLORING: Pomeranian, Maltese mix; red with white.

SIZE: Vash is about 12lbs and is full grown.

HISTORY: Vash was owner surrendered to us due to his owner not making arrangements for him in the move.

PERSONALITY: Vash is a true sweetheart, he is medium level energy and extremely shy. He likes to be on laps, but not like being held in mid-air. He does like to go on walks where there is not a lot of noise/activity.

TRAINING: Vash's previous owner said that he was completely housebroken and great on leash.

WOULD DO BEST: Vash would do best in an adult-only home that will build his confidence a little bit more because he is shy but wants to be with people. Vash would also prefer to have another dog.

CATS/DOGS/KIDS: Vash is great with cats and dogs. Due to his timidness Vash is not recommended for homes with children.

Vet Record: All of our dogs are currently vaccinated, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption.

AVAILABILITY: This dog is available for adoption now and is being fostered or kenneled in the San Fernando Valley area. Please email us and we will send you an adoption application. Local adoptions only (we do not ship dogs).

I am 55lbs, 6 years old and seeking my forever home!

Adoption Donation: $250

All dogs are microchippped, neutered, current on all vaccines, heartworm tested (if age appropriate) and up to date on preventatives at the time of adoption.

All household members and any dogs from the household need to be present at the time of your appointment.

The shelter is currently open by appointment only with an approved application. Please note, all applications are considered general and stay on file for 6 months. Specific animals are NOT put on hold for adoption. When you visit, the adoption counselors will be able to make suggestions based on the type of pet you are looking for and help you find the best fit for your family.

Animal House Shelter cannot guarantee the breeds of the adoptable animals. The animals are posted on the website as the breed or breed mix based on their physical characteristics they most resemble. We also cannot guarantee the ages of our adoptable animals or how large puppies will be when fully grown.

We look forward to seeing you soon!

attributes.descriptionHtml: Mango is one of our special needs kitties. She has lived in four different homes since her birth in 2015. Her early weeks were spent without her mother and surviving in a highly stressful environment outside before being rescued in Frisco. After extensive testing, doctors have diagnosed her with feline idiopathic cystitis (FIC), which is an inflammation of the bladder thought to be caused by stress. We still have hope she can find her forever home with someone that has had experience with this condition as she is so worth it. She is quite affectionate and loves to cuddle by your side. She would do best living alone. She doesn't mind children and has adapted to dogs but these triggers can cause her condition to flare up. If you believe you have the patience to pamper this little princess, please fill out an application at www.friscohumanesociety.com or call 972-498-8980.
